### 💡 Important Strategy for Amazon Logistics Professionals
1. **The VPD Step**: Universities like Cologne or TU Berlin often require you to apply for a **VPD (Vorprüfungsdokumentation)** via [Uni-Assist](https://uni-assist.de). This takes 6–8 weeks, so start this in **February 2027**.
2. **Work Experience**: Your Amazon experience is highly valued. Ensure your **CV** and **Statement of Purpose** highlight "Supply Chain Optimization" and "Data-Driven Logistics" to stand out.
3. **Credit Check**: Since you have a B.Tech in Civil Engineering, check if you have at least **15-20 ECTS in Statistics/Higher Math**. If not, you may need to take an online bridge course before applying.
